	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm not sure if anyone could use this but here's a basic DRAM circuit for 6502:
<br />
<br /><img src="http://img178.imageshack.us/img178/8994/dramfj6.png" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />It does 1 hidden refresh cycle per read/write, if you use a faster clock you can get in more refresh cycles by altering it to toggle /RAS after /RAS = 1 &amp;&amp; /CAS = 0
<br />
<br />Adjust the NAND gate for the JKFF's CLK active level

		

